text: Artificial insemination is when sperm is put into the cervix of a female to make her pregnant without sexual intercourse. It is often used for breeding livestock (animals). It can also be used in human insemination. It is the process of breeding without sexual intercourse. It is when the sperm of a male is extracted from the body and inserted the cervix and which in theory will make a woman pregnant. == Related pages == * Assisted vaginal delivery * In- vitro fertilisation (IVF) and Partner assisted reproduction (in-vivo fertilisation, sex) * Symphysiotomy Category:Biological reproduction Category:Pregnancy and childbirth Category:Medical procedures Category:Obstetrics and gynecology
title: Artificial insemination
